</ol>

<h4 id="remark-1">remark</h4>
<ol>
  <li>projective geometry is an elementary non-metrical form of geometry, meaning
that it is not based on a concept of distance.</li>
  <li>Projective geometry can also be seen as a geometry of constructions with a
straight-edge alone.  Since projective geometry excludes compass
constructions, there are no circle, no angles, no measuremetns, no parallels.</li>
</ol>

